  "prompt": "How do I convert 415V three phase to single phase?",
  "response": "To convert 415V three-phase power to single-phase, you have a few options:\n\n1. Use a three-phase transformer\n- Connects one phase and neutral to create single-phase power\n- Provides voltage reduction to standard single-phase voltage (e.g., 230V)\n- Requires professional installation\n\n2. Use a phase converter\n- Electronic device that converts three-phase to single-phase\n- Available in different types:\n  a) Static converters\n  b) Rotary converters\n  c) Digital phase converters\n\n3. Use two phases of the three-phase supply\n- Connect between two phases\n- Provides single-phase power with slightly different voltage\n- Requires careful electrical knowledge\n\n4. Use a three-phase to single-phase inverter\n- Electronic device that converts three-phase power\n- Provides stable single-phase output\n- More expensive option\n\nImportant safety considerations:\n- Always consult a licensed electrician\n- Ensure proper grounding\n- Follow local electrical codes\n- Use appropriate protective equipment\n- Match load requirements\n\nRecommendation: For precise conversion and safety, hire a professional electrician who can assess your specific electrical needs and implement the most suitable solution.",
